Job Description:
TITLE: Bioinformatics Analyst II (multiple positions)

DUTIES:

Work with Fred Hutch scientists to refine computational research questions and develop analytical processes that can be applied to genomic datasets:

Identify appropriate bioinformatics tools to meet the needs of proposed research projects.
Develop, test and implement standardized analytical pipelines to support common NexGen sequencing assays (e.g. RNA seq, ChIpseq, SNV/CNV, CRISPR screens, ChIP-seq profiling, single cell gene expression & epigenetic profiling).
Provide support to Fred Hutch researchers working with genomics data.
Work with genomics staff to ensure integrity and consistency of primary data and tracking of experimental details.
Provide figures and written sections describing methods and results for manuscripts, presentations, and grant applications generated by Fred Hutch researchers.

REQUIRES:

Masters degree in computational science, bioinformatics, genetics, or a related field or the foreign degree equivalent; and,
Three (3) years of professional informatics experience in a clinical research environment including three (3) years of each of the following:
Computational and statistical support for clinical research;
Analysis and interpretation of NGS datatypes including RNA-seq, miRNA-seq, and whole exome sequence;
Use of GATK best-practices workflows for variant calling in exome sequence data;
Consultation with researchers on robust experimental design;
Filtering and prioritizing of variants, SNVs, CNVs and gene fusion events;
Bulk RNA-seq analysis including alignment, feature quantification, QC and differential expression;
MicroRNA-seq analysis;
Relevant experience with shell scripting and proficiency with Python and R;
Experience with commonly used R packages (Bioconductor, ggplot, tidyverse).
Experience can be gained concurrently.

LOCATION: 40 hours/week in Seattle, WA.

APPLICATIONS:

E-mail resume to Fred Hutchinson Cancer Research Center at employment@fredhutch.org
